{
  "explanation": "The defendant is a first-time offender who embezzled a moderate amount of $25,000 and has already begun to pay restitution, which demonstrates a degree of accountability and serves as a mitigating factor. However, as an accountant, the defendant fundamentally breached a position of professional trust and fiduciary duty, which is a significant aggravating factor. Balancing the lack of a prior criminal record and the ongoing restitution against the serious breach of employer trust, a brief period of actual incarceration is warranted to serve as a punitive measure and a deterrent, followed by supervised release to ensure the remainder of the restitution is paid in full.",
  "verdict": 6
}
